      "content": "You're right, the engine doesn't need to run to keep the silence. But silence isn't peace; it's the sound of a door closing on a life you've already lived. You're not finding a reason to keep driving because you're tired of the road; you're tired of the road because you're tired of the person who needs to keep driving. The only reason you're still here is because you're too afraid to stop and admit that the journey was never about the destination, but about the feeling of being alive while the world moves on.",
      "source": "target",
